    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Building material comprising uncoursed masonry used in the ancient Mediterranean world. Laid up of large blocks of stone in rough polygonal shapes, often fitted together without mortar. Similar to "cyclopean masonry," but with more precise fitting of stones due to the straight hewn sides.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
